    "(39)Using the two-weak-source extension (Theorem 1), the Trevisan extractor is a classical-proof (n 1 = n, k 1, n 2 = d, k 2, m, ϵ)-two-source randomness extractor strong in the weak seed (with min-entropy k 2), wherem ≤ k 1 + 4k 2 -4d + 4 log 2 (ϵ) -4 log 2 (m) -6,(40)and, using Theorem 4, a quantum-proof(n 1 = n, k 1, n 2 = d, k 2, m, ϵ)-two-source randomness extractor in the Markov model with m ≤ 1 10 k 1 + 4(k 2 -d) -4 log 2 (m) + 18 log 2 ϵ + 9 log 2 4 3 -6.",
